
=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.7 ***
=====================================================================

--> LED, MagLED, RoSE, and RedDensGrad can be plotted.

=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.6 ***
=====================================================================

--> Labels for naming output files is changed.
      "2D" is added after the name of the field.

=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.5a ***
=====================================================================

--> Using figlet name.

=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.5 ***
=====================================================================

--> Added the molecular electrostatic potential to the properties
      evaluated.


=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.4 ***
=====================================================================

Some changes to the help menu and support for long command line
options (e.g. --help, and --version).


=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.3 ***
=====================================================================

 --> Added an option to put the atom labels in the plot. The new option
       is activated using "-l" or "-L".
 --> An improvement for the visualization of the gradient of LOL as a 
       vector field is made. 
       In this version, the size "V" of the vector "v" 
       is given by V=min(|v|,VMXS), where VMXS is calculated from the 
       physical dimensions of the molecule.
 --> In this version the *.gnp is not deleted by default. 


To do:

 --> program better values for the isolines depending on the 
       plotted field.
 --> further improve the visualization of the vector field (if needed)



=====================================================================
*** Version 1.0.2 ***
=====================================================================

 --> Small changes in the help menu to indicate the program handles
       automatically the cases where there is(are) only one(two)
       atom(s) in the wave function file.


To do:

 --> program better values for the isolines depending on the 
       plotted field.
 --> improve the visualization of the vector field



